The deadline to complete the 2020 Census questionnaire is quickly approaching! Residents have until September 30 to respond and be part of the count. Remember, the way billions of dollars are spent as well as the number of seats in Congress for our state will come down to each resident's participation in the 2020 Census.

By filling out the questionnaire, residents are helping our community receive future funding that can improve the quality of life in our community for years to come.

To access the questionnaire online visit https://my2020census.gov/ or call 844-330-2020.

Jarrell ISD operates an after-school program that is located at Igo Elementary and includes assistance with homework, indoor and outdoor games and other activities. If you are interested in an enrollment packet, jisd.afterschool@jarrellisd.org.

The program is open to students in grades PK-5th.

Please note: The after school program will not be open during virtual learning days when the campus is closed (August 19-September 8, 2020). The after school program will begin on September 9, 2020.

Attendance Alerts Update: With our current remote asynchronous learning method, student attendance can be earned from 12 a.m. to 11:59 p.m. each day. Teachers are given time to receive work, establish learning engagement and reconcile attendance until 10 a.m. the following school day.

If you are receiving alerts for attendance on your Ascender Parent Portal account by either email, text or a phone call, and you would like to stop receiving these alerts, please log into your Ascender Parent Portal account to make those changes.

Directions are available here: https://www.jarrellisd.org/UserFiles/Servers/Server_20996454/File/Parents%20Students/Registration/Ascender%20Parent%20Portal%20Alert%20Document.pdf
shared_text:
Jarrell Independent School District
August 24 at 3:24 PM ·

FYI Families: Attendance in a remote asynchronous learning environment allows students to establish attendance from 12 a.m. to 11:59 p.m. through measured learning engagement each day. With the extended time to gain attendance, teachers will be given more time to post attendance. This means attendance posted in Ascender may be subject to change as the teacher reconciles the student engagement later in the day.

This is the final week eligible families can apply for Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT). The P-EBT application is open through August 21, 2020.

P-EBT helps families get the food they need during the current pandemic by providing a one-time benefit of $285 per eligible child.

Families can apply by submitting an application to https://yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT (URL is case-sensitive).

post_text: Curbside Service begins at Igo Elementary today.
shared_text:
SCHOOLCAFE.COM
SchoolCafé

Jarrell Independent School District
August 18 at 12:02 PM ·

Child Nutrition will begin serving meals on Wednesday, August 19th from 10 – 11 am. Curbside service will be at Igo Elementary. Parents who are picking up meals for their children will need their child’s student ID so the meals can be properly charged to the student accounts. School campus rosters will be at curbside to assist students with ID numbers.

Jarrell ISD will be serving one breakfast and one lunch each day curbside. Students will have a choice between two breakfast and lunch entrees with a side and a choice of milk (white or chocolate).

No cash or checks will be accepted, only online payments through www.schoolcafe.com.

Meals will not be served on September 7 due to the Student/Staff Holiday.

Jarrell ISD will be serving one breakfast and one lunch each day curbside. Students will have a choice between two breakfast and lunch entrees with a side and a choice of milk (white or chocolate).

No cash or checks will be accepted, only online payments through www.schoolcafe.com.

Meals will not be served on September 7 due to the Student/Staff Holiday.

Beginning, July 1 curbside service will only be at Igo Elementary. Service will run two days (Mondays and Wednesdays) a week. Curbside pickup service will be from 12-1 p.m. There will be no neighborhood deliveries.

On Mondays, families can pick up Monday lunch, Tuesday breakfast and lunch, and Wednesday breakfast. Wednesdays will include Wednesday lunch, Thursday breakfast and lunch, Friday breakfast and lunch, and Monday breakfasts.

post_text:
Jarrell ISD families may be eligible to receive Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) benefits to buy food. The deadline to apply is June 30!

P-EBT is for children 5-18 years old who received SNAP food benefits for the month of March 2020 and children up to 21 years old who are certified for free or reduced-price meals at school in Texas during the 2019-20 school year. Children that attend a school that offers free meals to all students (Community Eligibility Provision or Provision 2) are also eligible.

Learn more: https://www.jarrellisd.org/news/district_news/pandemic_electronic_benefits_available

post_text:
Central Texans age 16-24 can connect with more than 60 virtual employers on June 17 at the Central Texas Virtual Youth Career Expo hosted by Workforce Solutions Capital Area and Workforce Solutions Rural Capital Area.

The virtual expo will highlight industries with in-demand occupations, showcase part-time, full-time and apprenticeship opportunities and share downloadable content for job seekers. The expo will also feature pre-recorded videos showing interview skills, how to write a resume, time management and more.

Register at bit.ly/wsrcavirtualcareerexpo to attend.

P-EBT is for children 5-18 years old who received SNAP food benefits for the month of March 2020 and children up to 21 years old who are certified for free or reduced-price meals at school in Texas during the 2019-20 school year. Children that attend a school that offers free meals to all students (Community Eligibility Provision or Provision 2) are also eligible.

Learn more: https://www.jarrellisd.org/news/district_news/pandemic_electronic_benefits_available

CHROMEBOOK Check-in Instructions and Schedule:

High school students must check-in their chromebooks on their scheduled days. Elementary and middle school students may drop off their chromebook during any of the dates/times listed below.

Wednesday, May 20, 12-3 p.m. - Seniors
Thursday, May 21, 9 a.m.-3 p.m. - Seniors
Friday, May 22, 9 a.m.-3 p.m. - 11th-graders and remaining seniors
Monday, May 25 - Memorial Day/School Holiday
Tuesday, May 26, 9 a.m.-3 p.m. - 10th-graders, remaining 11th-graders
Wednesday, May 27, 9 a.m.-3 p.m. - 9th-graders remaining 10th-graders
Thursday, May 28, 1-3 p.m. - Teachers
Friday, May 29, 9 a.m.-12 p.m. - Teachers

More information about the process is available here: https://www.jarrellisd.org/news/district_news/technology_check-in_schedule_and_instructions

Reminder: Starting this week, the district's Free Meal Service is moving to a 3-day a week schedule. Meals will be distributed ONLY on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays.

Families will receive the same number of meals weekly as before. We hope this change will be less burdensome on our families -- we know it can be difficult to get to the distribution locations 5 days a week. Distribution locations and times will remain the same, except for Jarrell Middle School. Starting Monday, meals will be distributed at JMS at the back of the school, in the bus lane. Please enter off Avenue C (by the Field House).
text:
Reminder: Starting this week, the district's Free Meal Service is moving to a 3-day a week schedule. Meals will be distributed ONLY on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays.

Families will receive the same number of meals weekly as before. We hope this change will be less burdensome on our families -- we know it can be difficult to get to the distribution locations 5 days a week. Thank you, Jarrell ISD Parents! Many of you have already completed our survey to help us plan for the coming weeks. It is very helpful.

post_text:
Jarrell ISD will be suspending normal school operations through April 3, with students returning to school on April 6.

There will be a press conference tomorrow at 11 a.m. at the Williamson County Courthouse that will address the county-wide and district services that will be available.

During this time, all Jarrell ISD facilities will be closed for instruction, including UIL events, athletics, rentals, field trips, and after-school. Additional information will be communicated as it becomes available, as there are a lot of decisions that need to be made.

We remain in communication with all Northern Williamson County school districts. More information will be coming soon.

Learn more: https://www.jarrellisd.org/departments/health_services/COVID19

TOMORROW: Parents and community members are invited to attend one of the two upcoming Cougar Community Conversations to hear from Superintendent Dr. Bill Chapman, Jarrell Elementary Principal Andrea David, Igo Elementary Principal Jack Wilson and Jarrell Middle School Principal Jeremy Hill as they address how the district and campuses are supporting student learning.

There are two opportunities to attend:

Wednesday, March 4 at 10 a.m in the MakerSpace at Igo Elementary
Wednesday, March 4 at 6:30 p.m. in the cafeteria at Igo Elementary
District leaders will talk about each school’s 2018-19 accountability rating, and what steps the district and campuses are taking to support student achievement, as well as student performance on standardized tests. The same information will be presented at both events, and Spanish translators will be available.

March 3, 2020 Primary Election information:

Last day to register to vote: Application must be postmarked by February 3, 2020.
Last day to apply for Ballot by Mail: Application must be received, NOT merely postmarked, in our office February 21, 2020 by 5pm.
Early Voting period: Tuesday, February 18, 2020 through Friday, February 28, 2020.
Election Day: Tuesday, March 3, 2020 - Polls open 7:00am to 7:00pm

For full details, including polling locations, read more: https://www.wilco.org/Departments/Elections
